{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17501273","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17501273"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T10:26:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T10:26:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1742"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1742","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1742"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.49,0.06,0.35,0.07,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1742"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108292"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1742","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1742"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1742"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90694"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"906"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"4953"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"9735"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12917"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"3415"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3453"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40433"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40580"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42379"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108292","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108292"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 65-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department via ambulance with a 30-minute history of crushing central chest pain, palpitations, and sweating. He has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDuring transfer from the ambulance to the resuscitation bay, he becomes unresponsive. His airway is patent, but he is breathing infrequently and irregularly in a gasping motion. His pulse is not palpable. The trace on the ambulance monitor (not capable of defibrillation) shows as below (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate immediate management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Chest compressions","Bag-valve-mask ventilation","Direct current cardioversion","Intravenous adrenaline","Precordial thump"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has suffered a cardiac arrest with ventricular fibrillation - a pulseless arrest rhythm, likely due to acute myocardial infarction. The patient is exhibiting agonal breathing, which should not be mistaken for normal or effective breathing. In any patient who is unresponsive and not breathing normally, \u003Cstrong\u003Echest compressions\u003C/strong\u003E should be the initial treatment after confirming cardiac arrest.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBag-valve-mask ventilation\u003C/strong\u003E is an important part of cardiopulmonary resuscitation but is not the initial treatment. Breaths should be administered after 30 chest compressions in a 30:2 ratio.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirect current cardioversion\u003C/strong\u003E is not indicated in ventricular fibrillation. Cardioversion differs from defibrillation in that it is synchronised with the QRS complex to revert tachyarrhythmias with a pulse. Defibrillation is not synchronised and is used for pulseless rhythms. While defibrillation is the definitive management, chest compressions should be performed while the defibrillator is being attached.  If a defibrillator is already attached (or time to defibrillation is realistically predicted at \u0026lt;20 seconds), three stacked shocks can be administered in witnessed VF/pVT arrests.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntravenous adrenaline\u003C/strong\u003E is administered after the second defibrillation attempt in shockable rhythms, or after the first rhythm check in non-shockable rhythms. It is not an appropriate immediate treatment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrecordial thump\u003C/strong\u003E is only recommended for witnessed, monitored, pulseless ventricular tachycardia arrests when defibrillation will be delayed and should not delay CPR. It is not recommended for ventricular fibrillation due to poor evidence for efficacy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Early chest compressions are the most important initial treatment in any cardiac arrest.","Agonal breathing should not be mistaken for normal breathing in cardiac arrest.","Defibrillation differs from cardioversion in that it is not synchronised to QRS complexes and is used for pulseless rhythms."],"references":["Australian and New Zealand Committee on Resuscitation, 2019. \u0022ANZCOR Guideline 11.2 \u2013 Protocols for Adult Advanced Life Support\u0022. https://resus.org.au/guidelines/","Nagpal AK, Pundkar A, Singh A, Gadkari C. Cardiac Arrhythmias and Their Management: An In-Depth Review of Current Practices and Emerging Therapies. Cureus. 2024 Aug 9;16(8):e66549. doi: 10.7759/cureus.66549. PMID: 39252710; PMCID: PMC11381938. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC11381938/","Ludhwani D, Goyal A, Jagtap M. Ventricular Fibrillation. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK537120/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90694"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1742"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"1860"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"1860","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/1860"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/acc89095-2d63-400d-88bc-44c988775ffa.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/acc89095-2d63-400d-88bc-44c988775ffa.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":473,"height":116}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90694","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90694"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-09T12:29:12+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-12T20:40:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1742"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108292"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://ap